<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Collapsing margins with padding/border</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#normal-block" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The top margin of the top most block box collapses as does the bottom margin of the bottom most block box without the presence of the padding or borders on the container." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                height: auto;
                width: .65in;
                background: green;
            }
            #d2
            {
                margin: 20px;
                height: 20px;
                background: white;
            }
            #d3
            {
                margin: 20px;
                height: 20px;
                background: white;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the elements on the page form the letter H.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2"></div>
            <div id="d3"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>